&lt;p&gt;Select a custom background image in zoom UI&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;in folder:
&lt;code&gt;~/.var/app/us.zoom.Zoom/.zoom/data/VirtualBkgnd_Custom&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;find the file with the name &lt;code&gt;{guid}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;replace the file with a link&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ln -s -f ~/Pictures/Backgrounds/dt-link.jpg &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;guid&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;use &lt;code&gt;wallpaper&lt;/code&gt; script at login/logoff to change the image before zoom runs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href="https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/how-to-write-a-script-to-change-zoom-background/"&gt;FreeCodeCamp&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>